Sender  Daltigoth~
Date    Tue Sep  3 18:06:10 2002~
Stamp   1031094370
To      all~
Subject Draon Punch, Hurricane Kick.~
Text
Well. I have been sitting and thinking. Scary idea, that, eh?
The complaint a lot of the high level people have about DP and HK
is that when they get 6 hits, the do -massive-
amounts of damage to the target.

The complaint monks have about 6 hit dragon punches and hurricane kicks
is that they give -massive- lag to the user, usually spelling the death of the monk
if their opponent is competent.

How about this. At the level that Dragon punch is supposed to get 5 hits
it gets the 30% chance per activation that the flaming flag activates, at the level of the user.
Some text like 'Your fist bursts into flame as you attack with your mighty dragon punch!'
Just like the flaming flag, it would do a bit of damage, and have a chance of smoke blinding.

At the level that dragon punch would get 6 hits
it would get something akin to a 20% chance of a 'sharp' flag type of damage boost.
Each hit of the dragon punch would do a noticeably larger amount of damage.
Text would read something along the lines of:
'As you strike with your dragon punch, you know you executed your technique PERFECTLY!'

Thus, dp would have a maximum amount of hits at 4, it would do less damage on average.
It would also give some interesting side effects which would make it worth having at high level.

For hurricane kick, the level 75 added effect would be lightning, along the lines of:
'Bolts of lightning fly from your legs as you attack with a mighty hurricane kick!'
As with DP it would be a 30% chance of activation, and have the small damage of the lightning
flag plus the chance to shock the target.

The level 90 boost would be the same as DP's. a 20% chance of damage increase...
'As you strike with your hurricane kick, you know you executed your technique PERFECTLY!'

An innovative solution, that would distinguish the skill even more from anything
else out there on other muds, as well as solving both the positive and the negative
problem of getting 5 and 6 hits with dragon punch and hurricane kick at high level.

I realize the imms are HUGELY busy with more important issues, but hey,
when their massive que of stuff gets lightened slightly, perhaps this idea has merit?

P.S.: By noticeable larger from sharp flag, I mean a max of about 60-70 more per hit.
Also, the fire/lightning flag would only activate once per use of the skill.
...I.E: 4 hit dp, 1 chance for boost activation.

-`8d`1.`!.`#.`8The end is the beginning is the end`#.`!.`1.`7
~
