Subject re:Tylyte~
Text
IN PK, people flee when they either:
a) are low in hp
b) getting away from charmies to blind them on entrance
c) theres a few dozen other reasons to flee also

But the thing is, when you flee.  You lag.
When someone lands fear on a demon/warrior, they
are thrown out've combat and given lag.  So that
the caster/follower can catch up and keep killing

In demons case, they can fear us when they're 
low on hp, then cast gate to a mob in an area they 
they know well, and being a warrior, if they're not in
the general area of "where", than you need to teleport
(t-port) to them.  Which causes lag.  Warriors get
no location skills.  So if a mage/cleric wants to get
away quick, all they do is teleport.  If any other
class wants to get away, they can fear then teleport
to somewhere they know well, then run through out other
areas until they can get back in safe.

Fear makes it easy for any class to make a
warrior impossible to chase after.  If someone flees
from narshe, course they goto haon'dor, but now they
have the choices of going to trollden, neo tokyo, midgaar, shadow groove
or draconian castle.  And unless you guess right, and can somehow still
have the ability to catch up to someone while spamming an
alias for "Where whoever", or if they're sneaked, just "where".  
that player, given any running skill at all, should not be
catchable by a warrior.  You don't need to heal when
running, you can just run circles around the mud

Yes this is more about warriors needed a "track" skill than
it is about fear making it easier for every class to get away from a demon.
~
