Subject fear~
Text
As Fascreth has stated, many of the above statements are true. However, as
recall, flee lag has been changed so that the flee'er has less lag to remove
fear locks (thanks to people complaining about draconian fear combos). I've
seen many PKers I've fought whom after I casted fear on, were still able to
walk into the room we were in and attack me again before I can pull off any
other command. Another thing, is that warriors are made to use locks and
kill their opponent with melee. Being a demon warrior, sure flashkick lag
sucks, but sooner or later with all that HP, you'll land one with 1 round
of lag and be able to trip the hell out of your opponent.

IMHO, I believe that if Fascreth's used these tactics he would been able to
kill me easily, as I being a 1ker human cleric not even having 2k HP fully
equipped. But I also believe that warriors need some sort of detection
skill to know where their opponents are headed. For example a tracking
skill that lets you know where your opponent is, but not the exact room,
rather, the area in which they are in. I think that is fair enough, I mean
come on, everyone has a gate mob to gate to. I haven't seen anyone land in
an area by gating to sphinxs. They all have favorite mobs to gate to.

Another concern is that I can take demon warriors with a bit of luck and
skill but there is no way I can take a demon with backstab/circle or even a
monk that can land a 6-hit 1.5k dmg dragonpunch. Some of you may look at it
and say "well a 1ker shouldn't be able to take a well built character, even
if the PKer is skilled"... think again. Remember, we don't have the time to
put 8+ hours/day into a character, this game is supposed to be a GAME not
your LIFE. If a 1ker built properly could take other PKers regardless of
class/race but still have some difficulty its fine. But being, impossible
is intense. A 1ker human warrior can take a 10k esper cleric or even a
dragonkin monk if only they had flashkick/trip and outmelee'd them, with a
little luck of course ;)

~
