Date    Mon Sep 16 12:11:06 2002~
Stamp   1032196266
To      all~
Subject AQ & PK~
Text
Ahight, not to be mean or anything, but no one else will probably
reply to those ideas in a nice manner, so I'll do it.  Leveling
off of PK doesn't work, because PKilling isn't regulated by an
imm, as is RP.  No imm grants people PK points.  In other words, I
could get one of my buddies, and we could whack eachother off 100
times in one day.  Or 50 times in two days, etc.  You get the 
picture.  It's too easily abused.  Perhaps if we had some
sanctioned PK, where an imm watched and granted PK points, that would
work.  But, as stated above, this doesn't help bring in new PKers,
it would just be an added benefit to those who already PK.

AQEQ.  Having AQEQ, or fear of losing it, does not play that much
of a part in PK.  Yeah, flame me for it.  How many current PKers
are loaded with AQEQ and QEQ?  And, on the other hand, how many
people are PK only for the AQ point benefit?  This too, has been
Easily abused.  More people aren't setting PK because they can
get AQEQ easier after they lose it, they do it so they can deck
out their char in AQEQ and re-create, or so they can sell it for
mass profit.

Pish, somethings never change, and somethings were never meant to.
No, I'm not sorry this note is too long, heh.  The ideas are probably
good ones, it's just the tendency for players... PK or Non... to
abuse anything implemented defeats the purpose.  Imms don't 
change things, because no matter what, someone will complain.
Imms don't run quests every five seconds, because no matter
what, someone will complain.  How many people actually respect
what an Imm has to say?  Furthermore, how many Imms deserve that
sort of respect?

My point:  Yes, this might be just a game.  But there are, like
it or not, real people behind these characters.  If you don't
like it, there are thousands of other muds.  Leave.  Simple as
that.

-`1Redn`!e`1ck``
~
