Subject Lack of an idea.~
Text
Is it possible to implement something in pk that won't :

A.)Be abused by players.
B.)Just be there to stroke an ego.

If you recall, I've tried to run a few pk only quests.
I'm no master of imagination and I get lazy.
I have noticed that, when a reward is offered people do pk more.
I've also noticed that when a reward -is- offered, most nonpks don't think of it as worthwhile and pkset.

That comes back to me as "You're not doing anything wrong. We just don't want to pk."

I could setup a spiffy quest, which I -do- have like 3 sitting on the shelf. And one can come soon if I get some help with it.

Basically, nonpks don't want to pk unless the system changes significant.
Pks don't want the system to change significantly because it'd lose familiarity.

And so, even if a new pksystem was placed in, the neverending battle for players to find loophole begins.

Players expect something perfect, from an imperfect mud.

Most people who play now, use little imagination at all.
And that's where everything's gotta start from.

The mud faces a heavy battle between imagination vs unwillingness to change.

Now how's that suppose to change?
I have a couple undeveloped ideas. But people don't want to listen to me anymore, apparently.
~
