Sender  Batanen~
Date    Sat Sep 28 11:08:28 2002~
Stamp   1033229308
To      all~
Subject Weapons and Dam_nouns~
Text
Alrighty, folks.  I'm going to be writing at least a couple of idea notes
here, so bear with me.  It's sorta complicated, but I think it's what we
need to help bring new things and more fun stuff to AnimeMUD.

So I'll start with weapons and dam_nouns.  It's been agreed upon, and
even researched by Fatetaf that we've got a lot of weapon types not used
much at all.  It's also been agreed upon that we need to fix this, and should
do so.  So, that'll be the first thing we should attack in stock weaponry.
Adding new weapons (not weapon types) for the under-represented weapon
types.  Also, we've got a distinct lack of dam_nouns as well.  Not
a big variety....

So, we should add some new damage types, and dam_nouns to go with it.
Some of the balancing problems is due to the limited amount of damage
types we use.  Holy, negative, lightning, magic and fire tend to be our
primary damage types.  We should expand this list, and add a few new ones
to give more options for changing spells, skills, and weapon dam_nouns.

The ones that I'd like to add would be earth, wind, and water.  We'd also
expand the use of lesser used damage types.  By doing this, we can get rid
of some of the generics we've got in stock, and give both magic and weapons
a kick-in-the-pants flavor hit.  There's also another reason do to this, and
that's the idea I've had for a new class.  Note, that I think this is
a good idea even w/o the class, because it allows for more options
damage wise.

My next note will be an introduction to the class I'd like to add, and
their class skills that makes them different than the other classes.


Batanen Fujioka
~
Sender  Batanen~
Date    Sat Sep 28 11:24:37 2002~
Stamp   1033230277
To      all~
Subject New Class Proposal~
Text
The first idea introduced the idea of adding more damage types, specifically
elemental ones.  To this, I'd like to propose a melee style class that
would be able to manipulate those elements to his/her protection and
offense, the Shaman.

The shaman would be a fighter-mage hybrid class.  It's specialty would
be using the elements to enhance his armor... but also his weapon.  Spells
to attack would be available, but not nearly as powerful as the mage.

New Spell Group:  Elemental Shielding
This spell group would be exclusive to the Shaman, and it would allow
for different elemental shields that would create a temporary resist to
an element.  There would be different spells for different elements, and only
one elemental shield could protect a person at a time.

New Spell Group: Elemental Offense
This spell group would be available to mages and shamans.  This would be the
offensive section of spells that the shaman can cast.  It would help to
fill the void with low and mid level spells.  These would not be as strong as
say, slayers or gravity arcana, but would be effective if used in
conjunction with a possible vuln.

New Spell Group: Elemental Weapon Imbue
The shaman would be able to imbue temporarily his own weapon with a spell
that would change the dam_noun of the weapon to the element, and add on
the element's weapon affect.  Like fire would add flaming, etc.  All of
the elements would have a specific weapon affect that could get added
to the weapon.  This makes weapon choice for the shaman much more
interesting, and makes their melee attacks much more vicious.

My current guess on elements would be the following:
Fire, Water, Wind, Earth, Lightning, Cold.

The stock selection of skills and spells would be something to be discussed
amongst everyone, to make sure this class is properly balanced.


Batanen Fujioka
~
