To      all~
Subject Ideas instead of Shaman (#1)~
Text
I'm against another class like a Shaman.  

I think the classes need more skills, and no
class has 3 whole spell groups just for themselves.

I think we should add about 10-15 (yes this is a lot)
new skills/spells to each class.  THEN work on a new 
class.  Why?  Because right now 100% of the playerbase
isn't the new class.  And we should improve the current
classes before making a new one that will be better than
the rest.  Better because he'll have new spells only 
accessible to them.

Currently its..

Mages --> Slayers & Draconians. 
Slayers are group of 3 spells.  Why not add onto this?  

Draconians are based off HP instead of mana.  And even on
chars with lots of HP for a mage, aern't worth using.

Ninjas --> Smoke Bomb. 
Smoke Bombs cool, but it was nerf'd and now it misses too much.

Thieves --> Backstab.
Thieves get a lot've cool stuff, charmies, etc.  They've got a lot
to work with.

Warriors --> Rapid Strike, Counter-Attack, Bash.
Rapid Strike is soso.  Its usable to a point, but even
with a 65avg dam_magic and 134/166 rolls.  It rarely
does unspeaks to a mobile unsanc'd.  I'd say it averages
about 550.  Through sanc thats 225.  In pk thats about 
150.  Most chars would average 120 I believe.

Counter-Attack, is fine.  very useful.

Bash is worthless, lvl 40 mobile could bash lock a lvl 90
dragonkin warrior.  But a lvl 90 Demon has trouble bashing
a lvl 74 Vamp/Ninja.  

Clerics --> Healing, Harm, Weather
Healing is cool.  Not leet like Heal Touch, but leet enough.

Harm sucks, I don't think any cleric in his/her right mind 
would use this.  

Weather is "okay".  I mean, Faerie Fire is nice.  Nothing else
is though.

Monks --> Heal Touch, Dragon Punch, Hurricane Kick
HealTouch is the best healing skill in the game.  Lucky them.

Dragon Punch is most damaging starting attack in the game by a
good 1200-1500 damage.

Hurricane Kick is *also* most damaging starting attack.  But 
most people can't afford the equipment to have 3k+ mvs.  Let
alone enough to make it outdamage DP on most stock chars.

---------------------------------------------------------------

Heres what I suggest we change/add.  I'm sure many people will 
cry, moan, what not.  But this is what I like.

Mages --> Elemental,Illusion, 
(I'm not sure if we already have an Illusion group)

Elemental - We break apart Combat Spells.  And take
the basic spells, and maybe make 3-4 spell group areas
of this.  Or maybe make it a large spell group, worth
9CP.  But it would contain, say, 16-20 spells.  Every
15 or 20 some odd levels.  The player gains 4 spells
from this group.  Heres a rough example

Lvl 5:
(Fire) Burning Hands - Low level, damaging spell.  One hit
unless the char is past lvl 45.  Then it gets 2 hits for 
each hand.  Small chance of firebreathing the user.

(Water/Ice) Chill Touch - Low level, damaging spell.  One 
hit, has an affect to do the chill affect on a person/mobile
and the damage is about 1/2 that of Burning Hands.

(Earth) Tremor - Sort of like earthquake.  Causes a minor 
tremble in which the person has a chance of being "trip'd"
or thrown to the ground so they have to type stand.  

(Lightning) Shocking Grasp - More or less Burning Hands, 
different damage type.  Has a chance of shocking the user
and ceasing all there attack/spells for the next round.

Level 25:
(Fire) Fireball - Basically what it is now.

(Water/Ice) Arctic Blast - Ice fog type affect that will
cast chill touch and chance of blinding user.  Does the
damage of say a spell 10 levels lower than it.  

(Earth) Boulder - Boulder is created, more or less smashes
the target.  Has a chance to knock the user down.  More
of a hard damaging spell.  The damage WOULD be physical here.
As I think most "earth" spells should be.

(Lightning) Bolt - Target is hit by bolt of lightning.  Causes
them to take a strong hit of damage.  Chance of being affected
by the shock affect.  

Level 65: (FB=Firebreath)
(Fire) Inferno - Hits everyone in the room, aside from the 
~
