affect in that certain room. 

(Water/Ice) Blizzard - Basically the D2 spell.  A huge ice
storm sweeps in and targets everyone in that area.  Causing
minor amounts of damage over a long time.  It would be sort
of like chain lightning.  But would only hit the users 3
times per cast, over say a time of 2-3 rounds.  Would have
1 or two rounds of lag.  Spammable, and a very good room 
clearing spell.

(Earth) Quake - Sort of like Earthquake.  Not mana dependant,
and does good damage.  Can randomly affect users with a trip
like status.

(Lightning) Chain Lightning - Keep it as it is.  Coolest 
spell all mages have IMO.

Level 80:
(Fire) Apocalypse - Basically the OLD diablo spell without
the area affect.  Can be cast TWICE in one round at level
90.  Does a lot of fire damage.  Large chance of FB and
heavily affects the vuln_ of a user.

(Water/Ice) Avalanche - Calls down a avalanche.  You cast
the spell and theres one round wait.  The next two rounds
after the spell is cast the victim is hit by up to 8 hits
and a 50% chance each of being put into a trip or on the
ground status.  If the user is tripped he is instantly
affected by chilltouch affect.  If the mage is killed, the
spell still happens.  If the mage is pushed out of combat
somehow, the spell is interupted.

(Earth) Asteroid - Some might call this "Fire".  But it
would basically cause random hits in the rooms around the
caster.  And in the room he is in.  Caster has a chance of
being hit.  Spell lags the caster for 3 rounds.  Spell will
not land on mobs in combat.  Unless the player is PKset or
something like that.  I know this is codable, cause they have
a spell semi-like this in another MUD I play.

(Lightning) Surge - STRONG and quick spell.  Mage takes one
round of lag and loses 1/5th the dmg done to the person who
the spell was casted upon.  This would be a quick spell and
probably a great finisher for a mage.

Illusion - More or less tricks on the other player/mobiles
eyes.  Would make it harder for the mage to be hit, or help
them escape.

Project Image - Caster can cast this, and it creates a fake
him in that room.  Caster can make two of these at level 90.
If the "Image" is attacked.  It instantly disappears and the 
user is not lagged at all from this attack.  

Mislead - The caster casts this, the spell is hidden from the
victims eyes.  The caster flees the opposite way of which it
says he is fleeing.  ie:
Coco has fled!
Coco leaves to the west

Coco would really be leaving east.

Shadow Door - The caster would be seen casting gate, or
muttering hte wor "pahz" or whatever it is.  And would
appear to step through it.  Ceasing all combat in the
room.  But in reality he would still be in the room.
And the user would have to reinstate combat.
This is just the Mage ideas.  I have Ninja/Warrior done, and halfway
through cleric, I'll post ninja later.
