Subject Ideas instead of Shamans #3~
Text
Thats the *basic* I could think about mages.  I could go on forever
but I want to get into new classes.  I know this sounds like a lot
to code.  But even if you just stole the code from other spells in
the mud and changed there damage a bit.  No one would really care.


Ninjas --> Throw, Strikes, Chaining,

Throw: Like the Ninjas from Final Fantasy.  Would be a skill where
you throw a weapon, and it stays in the target until it is dead or
the player somehow gives you it back.  So you wouldn't want to go
and throw Herons into players.  But maybe Graedus's and what not.

Damage would be pretty basic.  Multiply the weapons avg dmg by 3,
figure a 50 avg would have a chance of doing 150 dmg.  Then add
two damage per damroll, and .5 dmg per hitroll.  So a 100/120 
ninja would get about  320 damage from a thrown weapon.  Any hit/
dam thats on the weapon itself would be multiplied by 5 or so.
So a 10/10 graedus thrown from a ninja who has 100/120 rolls would
hit for around 375.  That aint a whole lot, but it's good damage. 

Give the THROW skill 5 different places to "hit".
75% Chance it lands on chest.  Doing 100% damage.
10% Chance it lands on arm or lower. Doing 75% damage.
10% Chance it lands on the head.  Doing 150% damage.
4%  Chance it lands on the neck.  Doing 175% damage.
1%  Chance it misses.  The Ninja auto-retrieves the
weapon and is stuck with 3 rounds of lag.

Also, give different weapon types a special affect.

Swords- 10% chance the sword impales the target.  Causing an added
25% damage to the attack.

Daggers- 10% chance the dagger pierces very deep.  Causing an added
20% damage to the attack.

Axe-  10% chance the axe breaks through the AC of target.  Causing
the AC to be ignored and causing more damage.

Polearm-  5% chance of a double hit on the target.  

Spear- 40% chance ther target is impaled.  Causing 35% damage added.

Mace- 25% chance of causing target to be knocked down to the rest 
position.  10% enhanced damage if this happens.

Flail- 5% chance the weapon hits again.  

Exotics-  Heres the cool thing.  Can't throw exotics.  :)

Strikes: Ninjas are sort've like monks.  Trained in martial arts, so
they know a certain amount of punch/strikes.

Lvl 2:
Cats Paw - Basic Strike, does low amount of damage.  scratch dam_noun.

Lvl 10:
Eagle Talon - Stronger Strike, still scratch dam_noun.

Lvl 25:
Training Basics - Passive skill that will add an area into your prompt
where it would say "COMBO".  Allowing the fighter to do up to TWO strikes
in one round.  Make it a bar type skill, going slowly up the more you fight.
Like a limit break, or make it something that will randomly occur.

Lvl 40: 
Shark Bite - Two hit attack that does quick damage.  2 rounds of lag.

Lvl 48: 
Tiger Claw - Strong fire_dam attack.  Not quite as damaging as shark
bite but it has a chance of temporarily blinding the target.

Lvl 60: 
Aura Bolt - A skill that launches a burst of dam_holy/dam_light at the
target.  Causing intense damage.  

Lvl 75: 
Training Advanced - 
Allows the Ninja to chain 3 strikes in one round.

Lvl 80:
Mantra - Healing skill, will sacrifice 9/10 the Ninjas HP and heal the
players/mobiles in his group to 85% health.  

Lvl 89:
Bum Rush - Sabins old skill.  Up to 4 attacks, attacks up to three 
targets total

Lvl 90:
Training Complete - Allows the Ninja to chain 4 attacks into one. 

