To      all~
Subject Frog~
Text
Ahight, just a few quick wry comments and things to think
about.  First of all, Go Fas!  Hey, at least he's trying.  I
can't help but feel sorry for him though, as others, myself included
have tried something similar, to no end.  But hey, pester until
someone eventually gets annoyed enought to care, and you might
just accomplish something.  Anyways, carry on Fas, we're
routing for you all the same.  Second, a little idea that will
likely not happen, but that Kevin is kinda touching on on
9010.  That is single-round combat.  Or rather, anything you type
in, only applies to the current round of combat.  For example:
currently he has it set (or last I was on 9010), that Rapid Strike
can hit up to three times in one round, simply by spamming Rapid
three times.  However!  The user gets more lag, based on how many
times he has used it... making it more or less a finisher type
move, as he really wouldn't want to get that kind of lag in the
middle of combat.  My suggestion is thus:  Make all skills/spells
act in the same way.  If a Monk spams DP twice in one round, the 
first one goes through, the second one returns with 'you are already
in the process of Dragon Punching!'  Or something of the sort.  Okay,
lets try trip.  Trip misses, eck, lots of user lag for no result.
How about trip misses, and you get another chance to trip... if you
want to.  If that misses, your lag is greater, but if it hits, you
both get lagged.  In effect... if you're still following me, combat
would be slowed to a more managable speed.  This should, in theory
work with all skills and spells.  I know, it'd probably take a ton
of coding, but if Kevin is already working on something similar
it shouldn't be too difficult to adapt it to other things.
Along with this would go his new saves code, though it currently
only affects spells, I think it should affect skills as well.
Things would be severely more diversivied, more challenging, and
above all else, more fun.  Comments, questions, or flames?  Let
me know what you think.  I know I kinda rushed this note, but
I have homework to do.  So if I need to elaborate, let me know.

-`1Redn`!e`1ck``
P.S. Formating sucks, but I was in a hurry.  Sorry : P
