would spread out a bit more.

Enhancements - Skills that use warriors movement to forge a blade with a
certain affect.  The number of affects that would be temporarily added to
the blade would be enhanced on the level of the warrior.  Works somewhat
like envenom, without the total sucking.

Lvl 45:  1 Enhancements
Lvl 90:  2 Enhancements

Heres a list of the Enhancements:

Lvl 2: Poison, adds the poison flag to a weapon for 3 ticks per level.  So
a lvl 90 would allow it to last for 270 mud "hours".  

Lvl 15: Frost, adds a frost flag to a weapon for 3 ticks per level.  Etc.

Lvl 25: Flame, adds a fire flag to a weapon, 2 ticks per level.

Lvl 40: Charge, adds a shock flag to a weapon, 2 ticks per level.

Lvl 60: Sharpen, adds a sharp flag to a weapon, 1 tick per level.

Lvl 80: Enchant, adds a vorpal flag to a weapon, 1/4 tick per level.

Pretty basic.  Would make a lot of weapons better for warriors, and overall
make them a better melee class for PK.  It wouldn't *break* a weapon, or have
a chance.  

Roar - The new Fear for a warrior.  Seeing as fear is only usable by a dragonkin
warrior or a feline warrior.  Roar would act on the same basis, but would rely on
dex and strength.  

~
Sender  Fascreth~
Date    Wed Oct  2 20:54:21 2002~
Stamp   1033610061
To      all~
Subject Ideas instead of Shamans #5~
Text
Clerics --> Following, Aura, 

Following- A group of spells, depending on the alignment of the character. 
Clerics are supposed to be more or less religious.  So these spells would
require the caster to be good or evil.  No neutral.


Lvl 5: 
(Good) Saibaths Prayer - Doubles the regain rates of the caster for two rolls.

(Evil) Corgans Curse - Damaging spell, adds the plague affect at level 30.

Lvl 20:
(Good) Ray of Truth - Same spell we have now.  This would force the alignments
like it should be.

(Evil) Demonfire - Stays the same.

Lvl 45:
(Good) Implosion - Based on the targets alignment, the damage multiplies.  
1000-800:    20% Absorbed to Health
799-550:     0% Absorbed to Health
449-350:     50% Damage done.
350-(-350)   80% Damage done.
-350-(-700)  100% Damage done.
-701-(-900)  125% Damage done.
-900-(-1000) 150% Damage done.

(Evil) Creeping Doom - A very strong status affect, every 15 levels the affect
time of this spell increases 1 tick.  Takes 1/15th of the targets total health off
per tick.  Can be easily dispelled, and is even harder to land.  

Lvl 75: 
(Good) Blinding Light - A beam of light is blasted from the heavens, more or less
causing evil align targets to be blinded.  More like a stronger blindness spell and
causes small amounts of damage to target.

(Evil) Damnation - Target is hit with a spell with the opposite damage of Implosion.
Except the damage is fire, and has a chance of blind, firebreathing, and cursing the
target.

Lvl 90: 
(Good) Gods Will - Creates an exotic weapon.
dam_holy, vorpal and shocking.  

(Evil) Evils Awl - Creates an exotic weapon.
dam_negative, vorpal and fire.

Auras-  Sort've like the Paladins skill from Diablo2.  But you cast these, and can only
have one on you at any time.  Maybe make them effective with anyone/thing in your group also.

Lvl 20:
Redemption - Every round of combat, the Cleric is healed 15% of the damage taken during
the previous round of combat.  

Lvl 35:
Conviction - For every level of the caster, take away 1/4th a save from the target they
are currently fighting.  So at level 90 this spell would take way 22 saves.  

Lvl 50: 
Blockify - Dunno a name for this, but for every level it adds 3-4  to your -AC.  
so at lvl 90 this could be 270, or 360.  I think 270 would be better. 

Lvl 75:
Vengeance - For every physical hit taken.  The attacker recieves .2 damage per level they
are.  Pretty basic, would be nice for warriors who hit 10 or so times a round.  It would 
add up very quick along with spells.  
~
